I hate seeing repeated code structures.  We could simplify the mark() entry in 
plenty of PMCs with a macro something like:

#define MARK_UNLESS_NULL(interp, struct, name) \
    if (struct->name) \
        pobject_lives(interp, (PObj *)struct->name)

-- c

